subSubSection.paragraph:
Biology. Mainly species of Cerambycidae , Curculionidae and Buprestidae ( Coleoptera ) as host, but one species of Sesiidae ( Lepidoptera ) and two species of Argidae ( Hymenoptera ) are reported as well ( Marshall 1890 ; Rühl 1911 ; Fahringer 1926, 1934; Krogerus 1941 ; Györfi 1943 ; Schimitschek 1944 ; Watanabe 1954 ; Starý 1957 ; Tobias 1971 ; Filippenkova 1971 ; Shenefelt 1978 ;
Capek et al . 1982
; Haeselbarth 1983 ; Uhthoff-Kaufmann 1990 ; Campadelli et Scaramozzino 1994 ; Urano et Hijii 1995 ;
Wang et al . 2009
;
Yu et al . 2016
); in China reared from larva of
Ips typographus ( Linnaeus, 1758 )
( Coleoptera : Curculionidae ),
Monochamus sutor ( Linnaeus, 1758 )
and
Semanotus bifasciatus (Motschulsky, 1875)
( Coleoptera : Cerambycidae ).

Note. Watanabe (1950) reported this species from Shanxi (NW. China );
Sheng et al . (1992)
reported this species from Nei Menggu (NW. China ); Yang (1998) reported this species from Henan (NE. China );
Wang et al . (2009)
reported this species from Heilongjiang (NE. China ), Hubei (C. China ), Nei Menggu (NW. China ), Shandong (NE. China ) and Shanxi (NW. China ).
